Subject: BUG: VHDL compiler fails to compile variable assignments
To: atacs-bugs <atacs-bugs@vlsigroup.ece.utah.edu>
Content-Type: multipart/alternative; boundary=00032555a3da9c6fd904a31d2129

--00032555a3da9c6fd904a31d2129
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1

Currently, the variable assignment in a process, like the expression
"cnt:=cnt+1" in the example shown below, is not correctly compiled into an
LPN assignment. The "cnt" on the right hand side is not instantiated.

count: process (x)
  variable cnt : integer := -1;
begin
  cnt:=cnt+1;
end process;



-- 
Zhen Zhang

--00032555a3da9c6fd904a31d2129
